<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
  <p class="mb-6" style="color: var(--color-text-light);">Last updated: March 6, 2026</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-primary);">What Information We Collect</h2>
  <p class="mb-4">We collect minimal information to operate this site:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2">
    <li><strong>Contact forms:</strong> When you submit a contact form, resource submission, or newsletter signup, we collect the information you provide (name, email, message). These forms are processed by <a href="https://formspree.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Formspree</a>.</li>
    <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> We may use privacy-friendly analytics to understand how visitors use our site. No personal data is tracked.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Caregiver Gig Board</h2>
  <p class="mb-4">When you post a gig or respond to one on the Caregiver Gig Board:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2">
    <li><strong>Gig posts:</strong> Your first name and gig details are displayed publicly. Your email address is stored securely and is <strong>never shown publicly</strong> — it is used only to forward responses from interested caregivers and to verify your identity when managing your gig.</li>
    <li><strong>Gig responses:</strong> When you respond to a gig, your name, email, and message are forwarded to the gig poster via Formspree. Your information is shared only with the poster of that specific gig.</li>
    <li><strong>Data processing:</strong> Gig submissions are processed by a Cloudflare Worker that stores gig data in our site's source repository. Gig data is retained until the gig expires or is closed by the poster.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-primary);">How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2">
    <li>To respond to your inquiries and messages</li>
    <li>To review and add submitted resources to our directory</li>
    <li>To send newsletter updates (only if you subscribe)</li>
    <li>To improve the site and its content</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Newsletter & Email Communications</h2>
  <p class="mb-4">When you subscribe to our newsletter, we collect your name and email address. We use this information solely to send you:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2">
    <li>Updates about new resources added to our directory</li>
    <li>Blog posts, community stories, and announcements</li>
    <li>Occasional information about events or programs relevant to the disability community</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="mb-6">We will never sell, rent, or share your email address with any third party for marketing purposes. You may unsubscribe at any time by contacting us at <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a> or by following the unsubscribe instructions included in each email. Upon unsubscription, your email will be removed from our distribution list.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Donations</h2>
  <p class="mb-6">Donations are processed through Every.org, a third-party platform. We do not directly collect or store your payment information. Please refer to <a href="https://www.every.org/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Every.org's privacy policy</a> for details on how they handle your data.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Information Sharing</h2>
  <p class="mb-6">We do not sell, trade, or share your personal information with third parties for marketing purposes. Form submissions are processed through Formspree, which has its own <a href="https://formspree.io/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a>. Donations are processed through Every.org.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Cookies</h2>
  <p class="mb-6">This site does not use tracking cookies. Third-party services embedded on this site (such as Google Fonts) may set their own cookies. See their respective privacy policies for details.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p class="mb-6">This site is intended for caregivers and adults. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Your Rights</h2>
  <p class="mb-6">You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of any personal information we hold about you by contacting us at <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a>.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p class="mb-6">We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated date.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Contact</h2>
  <p class="mb-6">If you have questions about this privacy policy, please <a href="/contact/">contact us</a>.</p>
</div>
